  "local_port": 43536,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I use WhatsApp on a PC?",
  "response": "Using WhatsApp on a PC is quite straightforward. You have two primary options: WhatsApp Web and WhatsApp Desktop. Here's how you can use both:\n\n### WhatsApp Web:\n1. **Open Browser**: Launch your preferred web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge, etc.).\n2. **Navigate to WhatsApp Web**: Go to [web.whatsapp.com](https://web.whatsapp.com).\n3. **Link Your Phone**:\n   - Open WhatsApp on your phone.\n   - Tap the three dots (menu) on the top right corner (Android) or go to Settings (iPhone).\n   - Select \"Linked Devices\" or \"WhatsApp Web/Desktop\".\n   - Tap \"Link a Device\".\n   - Use your phone to scan the QR code displayed on your computer screen.\n4. Once the QR code is scanned, your WhatsApp account will be mirrored on your PC.\n\n### WhatsApp Desktop:\n1. **Download WhatsApp Desktop**:\n   - Visit the [WhatsApp download page](https://www.whatsapp.com/download).\n   - Download the version applicable to your operating system (Windows or macOS).\n2. **Install**: Follow the installation instructions to install the software on your machine.\n3. **Link Your Phone**:\n   - Open WhatsApp on your phone.\n   - Tap the three dots (menu) on the top right corner (Android) or go to Settings (iPhone).\n   - Select \"Linked Devices\" or \"WhatsApp Web/Desktop\".\n   - Tap \"Link a Device\".\n   - Use your phone to scan the QR code displayed on your computer screen.\n4. Once the QR code is scanned, your WhatsApp account will be accessible via the desktop application.\n\n### Features:\nBoth methods allow you to:\n- Send and receive messages.\n- Share files and media.\n- Participate in group chats.\n- Use voice and video calling (if supported by the Desktop version).\n\n### Notes:\n- Keep your phone connected to the internet for the PC interface to work.\n- Ensure WhatsApp is up-to-date on both your phone and PC for optimal performance.\n\nBy following these steps, you can seamlessly integrate your WhatsApp experience between your mobile device and your PC.",
